  "prompt": "Knock knee cause any problem in Delhi police si selection?",
  "response": "Knock knees, medically known as genu valgum, can potentially be a disqualifying factor in various physical fitness and medical examinations, including those for positions such as Sub-Inspector (SI) in the Delhi Police. These examinations typically have stringent physical and medical criteria to ensure that candidates are fit for the demanding nature of police work.\n\nDuring the selection process, candidates undergo a thorough medical examination to assess their physical health and fitness. Conditions like knock knees may be evaluated by medical professionals to determine if they could impair the candidate's ability to perform duties effectively. If the condition is severe and deemed to affect the candidate's mobility or physical performance, it may lead to disqualification.\n\nHowever, the exact criteria and guidelines can vary, so it is recommended to refer to the official recruitment notification or consult directly with the Delhi Police recruitment authorities for precise information. If you have knock knees but believe they do not significantly impact your physical abilities, it might be worthwhile to seek a medical opinion from a specialist who can provide a detailed assessment of your condition.",
